Third-party software

This project depends on open-source packages (npm dependencies such as React,
WXT, Radix UI, Tailwind CSS, Lucide, and others). Those packages remain under
their own licenses (primarily MIT, Apache-2.0, BSD, and ISC).

A high-level summary of dependency licenses in a typical install:

  MIT, ISC, BSD-2-Clause, BSD-3-Clause, Apache-2.0, MPL-2.0, and dual-licensed
  packages as declared by their authors.

To regenerate a full dependency license inventory after `npm install`:

  npx license-checker --summary
  npx license-checker --production --relativeLicensePath

Bundled production builds include only the code that the bundler emits for
runtime dependencies; always consult each package’s own LICENSE file under
node_modules/ for authoritative terms.

